<paragraph id="3FBEEC9A21C2792F9A3CB32D60BB25F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
<taxonomicName id="5C502101B7A40AAAB9AD57DFD3372E05" authority="Fauvel, 1927" authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1927" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii Fauvel, 1927</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91AFE98BE8342C9F03CAE4DE6480ABBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="95BA595AAC4F1519D30DE19C1DA6153E" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A27BA21220C120DC7156DADF2519B6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation id="A6D48BAB0A467D758559636B5A5FF3B1" author="Papageorgiou, Nafsika" journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="643 - 653" title="Multicausal environmental severity: A flexible framework for microtidal sandy beaches and the role of polychaetes as an indicator taxon" volume="70" year="2006">Papageorgiou et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. Type locality: Mediterranean (Agay, France). 
<taxonomicName id="39FC726E4A7F24272F220F1F0E615851" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
was initially described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="D802F7D7F00BB87FCEFC5EE518B1872C" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="radiata">Ophelia radiata</taxonomicName>
(Delle Chiaje, 1828) by 
<bibRefCitation id="544E76C861665CDCEF53A239E70ADC44" author="Fauvel, P." journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Faune de France. Polychetes sedentaires" year="1927">Fauvel (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, who distinguished the European species of 
<taxonomicName id="E529D1FFAA0C0B48E0D56981769B05A7" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Ophelia</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="0AA2C6317E5994B99E9D2BA986764D81" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia neglecta" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="neglecta">Ophelia neglecta</taxonomicName>
Schneider, 1892, Savigny, 1822, 
<taxonomicName id="C8F6B562BD22A10533C9AAA19B529EB4" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="radiata">Ophelia radiata</taxonomicName>
(Delle Chiaje, 1828) and 
<taxonomicName id="3325B49A658687DD1026E762E08285B0" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
) on the basis of the number of gill pairs. This was regarded as an unreliable character by subsequent authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="0E538E53FADDE6660B8A5643401546E5" author="Bellan, Gerard" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Universite d'Aix-Marseille, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Contribution a l'etude systematique, bionomique et ecologique des Annelides Polychetes de la Mediterrannee" year="1964">Bellan 1964a</bibRefCitation>
) who considered 
<taxonomicName id="20D8CB1AA630FB9498E160916AF898F2" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="radiata" subSpecies="barquii">Ophelia radiata barquii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3AC4863317F95D5E06D5DF36C07BCD1B" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="radiata">Ophelia radiata</taxonomicName>
synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E78A884ECD13424EB3EBC92758DDE7" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
. However, molecular and morphological analyses by 
<bibRefCitation id="647EB19301547D2272F89B5BA1E98925" author="Maltagliati, F." journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="101 - 113" title="Morphological and genetic evidence supports the existence of two species in the genus Ophelia (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Western Mediterranean" volume="83" year="2004">Maltagliati et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="24A2BF49DB67B7DD87A78B7C891A072A" author="Maltagliati, Ferruccio" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="835 - 841" title="Taxonomic distinction of Opheliabarquii and O. bicornis (Annelida: Polychaeta) in the Mediterranean as revealed by ISSR markers and the number of nephridiopores" volume="85" year="2005">Maltagliati et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
clearly differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="7F969F37FB8122ECB080DB5724408CA9" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="45F7033269875F768E41F0455967322B" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
, the constant morphological difference between the two species being the number of nephridiopore pairs (five in 
<taxonomicName id="9F37553AAD0E837E6F6299EF91972ED7" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
, six in 
<taxonomicName id="B60F5BCC825607D0B2264955E1F9D14E" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
). See also comments under 
<taxonomicName id="7B5751E1384FE6D0F4096E382D78F667" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
